 "title": "Curry pork braai chops – my finest hour",
 "excerpt": "I grew up with my mother marinating chops in a curry sauce with lots of onion. She liked to use pork chops. Out on the farm the chops sat in the fridge for a long time – sometimes up to a week. I just let mine sit overnight and it was …",
 "seo": {
  "title": "Curry pork braai chops - my finest hour - Marinda Kook",
  "description": null
 },
 "html": "<p>I grew up with my mother marinating chops in a curry sauce with lots of onion. She liked to use pork chops.  Out on the farm the chops sat in the fridge for a long time &#8211; sometimes up to a week.  I just let mine sit overnight and it was heeeeeeeavenly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>YOU NEED:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>6 pork chops<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-011.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-813\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 011\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-011-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>30 ml oil</li>\n<li>2 onions</li>\n<li>7.5 ml ground coriander (optional)</li>\n<li>30 ml curry powder</li>\n<li>15 ml turmeric<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-013.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-824\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 013\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-013-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>30 ml sugar</li>\n<li>60 ml vinegar</li>\n<li>30 ml apricot jam</li>\n<li>500 ml water<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-017.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-814\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 017\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-017-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>NOW:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>pour the oil into a pan on the stove<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-002.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-811\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 002\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-002-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>slice the onions into rings <a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-005.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-812\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 005\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-005-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>fry the onions until glassy and sprinkle the coriander over &#8211; fry for another 3 minutes<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-016.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-822\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 016\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-016-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>mix the curry powder, turmeric, sugar, apricot jam, vinegar and water in a bowl<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-815\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 021\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-021-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>pour it over the onions and cook for 5 minutes<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-023.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-826\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 023\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-023-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>pour some of the sauce into the bottom of your braai dish as a base <a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-028.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-816\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 028\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-028-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>now layer the chops in your braai dish and store in the fridge<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-038.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-818\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 038\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-038-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The next day or evening, get a lovely fire going.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-071.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-823\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 071\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-071-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a>  Once the coals are ready, lay your meat on the grid.  Braai now until the fat on the meat is nicely done.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-092.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-820\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 092\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-092-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a>  Put the meat back in your braai dish and warm it through in the sauce over the fire. Let it simmer through a little.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-099.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-825\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 099\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-099-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>Don't hold back.  Eat heartily and enjoy.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-112.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-819\" alt=\"kerrietjops en bloukaaskool 112\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/kerrietjops-en-bloukaaskool-112-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>"
}
